description: TEHRAN- A survey by the Palestinian Center for Policy and Survey Research (PSR) shows support for Hamas and the armed struggle to end Israeli occupation rose over the last three months.
title: Rise in Palestinian support for armed struggle

description: The director of Kamal Adwan Hospital in Beit Lahia, northern Gaza Strip, said there are more than 200 Palestinian children currently at risk of death due to malnutrition.
title: Over 200,000 children showing 'symptoms of malnutrition' in Gaza

description: Israel has committed more than 3,300 massacres against the Palestinians in the besieged Gaza Strip since October 7, claiming the lives of over 37,000 victims, a majority of them women and children, the government media office (GMO) in Gaza has said.
title: Israel committed 3,300 massacres against Gaza since 7 October: GMO

description: The Japanese Parliament, Thursday, adopted a resolution, calling for an immediate ceasefire in the Palestinian-besieged enclave of Gaza, Anadolu Agency reports.
title: Japan Parliament calls for ceasefire in Gaza

description: Former Israeli War Minister, Benny Gantz, accused Prime Minister, Benjamin Netanyahu, on Thursday of obstructing a prisoner exchange deal with Palestinian factions in the Gaza Strip for “political reasons”, Anadolu Agency reports.
title: Ex-Israeli war cabinet member accuses Netanyahu of hindering prisoner exchange deal

description: TEHRAN - In an analysis, Javan discussed a recent report by the Reuters news agency in which it claimed that Iran would give a limited response to the IAEA Board of Governors resolution.
title: Iran's response is decisive and proportionate

description: TEHRAN –Iran's acting Foreign Minister Ali Baqeri has held a telephone conversation with Saudi Arabia's Foreign Minister Faisal bin Farhan to discuss the different aspects of Hajj pilgrimage rituals.
title: Iranian, Saudi chief diplomats discuss Hajj arrangements

description: TEHRAN - In a phone call with Russian President Vladimir Putin on Thursday, Iran's Acting President Mohammad Mokhber congratulated Russia on its Independence Day and emphasized the strategic nature of Tehran-Moscow relations, built on enduring principles.
title: Iran, Russia reaffirm strong ties, vow to deepen cooperation

description: TEHRAN – Iran and the Republic of Azerbaijan conducted a joint military drill on Wednesday aimed at bolstering regional security and countering terrorist threats.
title: Iran, Azerbaijan stage joint military drill

description: TEHRAN – Leader of the Islamic Revolution Ayatollah Seyyed Ali Khamenei has addressed travelers beginning this year’s Hajj pilgrimage, highlighting the unifying and empowering nature of the Islamic rituals.
title: Leader emphasizes unity and resistance in message to Hajj pilgrims

description: TEHRAN – Iran and Iraq have jointly appealed to the international community to help end the ongoing conflict in the Gaza Strip.
title: Iran, Iraq urge international action to end Gaza conflict

description: TEHRAN – The Mujahedin-e-Khalq terror organization is facing increasing scrutiny as police around the world are tightening their grip on the group, with French police raiding MKO’s headquarters earlier this week.
title: MKO under growing pressure as headquarters raided again

description: TEHRAN – All six candidates running for president in the June 28 elections appeared on national TV on Thursday and Friday to answer expert questions on their plans and policies regarding the economy, culture, and politics.
title: Voters get in-depth look at candidate policies in TV roundtables, interviews

description: TEHRAN - A leaked audio recording of a former administrator at Columbia University in the city of New York has suggested that officials at the institution have tried to cover up chemical attacks against pro-Palestine student protestors.
title: Columbia University embroiled in scandal of chemical warfare

description: Russian President Vladimir Putin promised Friday to “immediately” order a cease-fire in Ukraine and begin negotiations if Kyiv started withdrawing troops from the four regions annexed by Moscow in 2022 and renounced plans to join NATO. Ukraine responded by calling Putin’s proposal “manipulative” and “absurd.”
title: Putin offers conditional truce

description: TEHRAN- Recent bombshell revelations about clandestine meetings between senior Israeli, American and Arab military officials have sparked widespread outrage and suspicion in the Muslim world, particularly among Palestinian people who view such secretive discussions as a betrayal of their cause amid the Tel Aviv regime’s genocidal war on the Gaza Strip.
title: Backstabbers

description: TEHRAN-Well-known Iranian-born British singer Sami Yusuf and renowned Iranian classical vocalist Homayoun Shajarian have collaborated on a new track that will be released soon.
title: Sami Yusuf, Homayoun Shajarian collaborate in new song

description: TEHRAN-The Tehran Symphony Orchestra (TSO) will stage its first concert in the current Iranian year (started March 20) before the beginning of summer at Vahdat Hall in Tehran.
title: Tehran Symphony Orchestra to stage “From the New World” concert at Vahdat Hall

description: TEHRAN- The Arabic version of Moustapha Akkad’s 1976 epic film “The Message” will be screened in Iran for the first time, with Persian dubbing.
title: Arabic version of Moustapha Akkad’s “The Message” to be screened in Iran

description:
* A collection of paintings by Shila Piran is on display in an exhibition at Tarrahan Azad Gallery.
The exhibition named “Enamel Citadel” will be running until June 25 at the gallery located at 5 Salmas Square, off Fatemi St.
title: What’s in Tehran art galleries

description: TEHRAN - Shabab Al Ahli come from behind to upset Shahrdari Gorgan and win 73-71, booking a spot at the BCL Asia 2024 Final at the Sheikh Saeed Bin Maktoum on Friday.
title: Gorgan fail to advance to BCL Asia 2024 Final

description: TEHRAN - After a 14-year hiatus, the Mashhad-Lar flight service has been re-established, fulfilling a long-standing demand for pilgrims traveling to the holy shrine of Imam Reza (AS).
title: Mashhad-Lar flights re-established after 14-year hiatus

description: TEHRAN - Sarouk carpets, renowned for their exceptional quality and enduring beauty, are among the most famous carpets woven in Iran’s Markazi province.
title: Discover distinct charm of Sarouk carpets

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s deputy minister of handicrafts has announced that handicraft exporters will be exempt from paying value-added tax (VAT).
title: Handicraft exports exempted from VAT

description: TEHRAN - Following a highly successful run in Beijing, Iran’s prestigious loan exhibit “Glory of Ancient Persia” has now opened in Shanghai to widespread acclaim.
title: ‘Glory of Ancient Persia’ highly welcomed by visitors in Shanghai

description: TEHRAN – Visiting Kordestan is a wonderful opportunity to experience a unique culture and meet people who proudly preserve their rich heritage.

description: TEHRAN - El Niño was the primary driver of extreme rainfall in April and May that caused widespread flash flooding across Iran, as well as Afghanistan and Pakistan, doubling the chance of extreme rainfall, a new World Weather Attribution study found.
title: Iran floods ‘driven by El Niño but probably exacerbated by climate change’: report

description: TEHRAN –The World Food Program (WFP) has released a report, expounding on activities in Iran over the month of May.
title: WFP releases May report on Iran

description: TEHRAN - Iranian Ambassador to Kuwait Mohammad Toutounchi and Kuwaiti Minister of Commerce and Industry Omar Saud Al-Omar have urged developing a roadmap to broadening trade exchanges.

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s economy grew by 5.7 percent in the fiscal year ending in late March 2024, marking the highest growth since 2017, according to the Statistical Center of Iran (SCI).

description: TEHRAN - The head of the agricultural commission of the Iran Chamber of Commerce, Industries, Mines and Agriculture (ICCIMA) said some $550 million of medicinal herbs were exported from the country last year (March 21, 2023 to March 19, 2024).

description: TEHRAN - Iran imported $92 million of car tires in the first two months of the current Iranian calendar year (March to May 2024), showing a 76 percent growth compared to the same period last year, a report said.

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s deputy oil minister said that 75 percent of the gasoline produced in the country complies with EUR 4 and 5 standards.
title: ‘75% of Iran’s gasoline output meets Euro 4, 5 standards’

description: TEHRAN - The Iranian Steel Producers Association (ISPA) said the steel production volume in the country in the first two months of the current Iranian calendar year (March to May 2024) registered a 1.6 percent growth compared to the same period last year.
title: Iran’s 2-month steel output up 1.6%: ISPA

description: TEHRAN - Head of Iran Chamber of Commerce, Industries, Mines, and Agriculture (ICCIMA) Samad Hassanzadeh has underlined the need for Iranian commercial attachés to make further efforts to boost the country’s foreign trade.
title: Commercial attachés urged to help Iran’s foreign trade

description:
The BRICS Sports Games have started in Kazan, the capital of the Republic of Tatarstan. The competitions will run until 23 June. The Games have never been held in Russia before. TV BRICS is the international information partner of the BRICS Games.
The start of the tournament itself was given by Russian President Vladimir Putin via video link.
title: BRICS Sports Games open in Russia

description: TEHRAN – Hossein Rasouli of Iran claimed a gold medal in the 2024 Asian Throwing Championships on Friday.
title: Hossein Rasouli wins gold at 2024 Asian Throwing Championships

description: TEHRAN- This year is the first year that Iran has formally joined the BRICS mechanism, which provides a new platform for China-Iran cooperation and enriches the vision and potential of the China-Iran comprehensive strategic partnership. From June 10th  to 11th, the BRICS Foreign Ministers' Meeting was held in Nizhny Novgorod, Russia.
title: China, Iran work together to increase value of BRICS
